Fix compatibility with gnu-efi >= 4.0.0

gnu-efi 4.0.0+ introduces several breaking ABI changes:
1. ReallocatePool argument order changed (handled via GNU_EFI_3_0_COMPAT in ebuild)
2. AsciiStrLen is now provided by gnu-efi (renamed from strlena) - remove duplicate
3. CompareGuid now has a macro in legacy/efilib.h - remove conflicting macro
4. CompareGuid return value semantics (handled via GNU_EFI_USE_COMPAREGUID_ABI=0 in ebuild)

References:
- https://sourceforge.net/p/refind/discussion/general/thread/de16ef94ef/
- https://github.com/ncroxon/gnu-efi/pull/25/commits/f3656c88007a775562b625a2cfe1bc54c1170bfe
- https://github.com/ncroxon/gnu-efi/pull/18/commits/ac8d6944c28ddb38bff44b4a5b5072a62682d313

Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/944562

